<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM7.11">
<l>mallai mānakark kiṟaiyavaṉ ṟaṉṉai vāṉce luttivan tīṅṅaṉa māyat</l>
<l>tellai yiṟpiḷḷai ceyvaṉa kāṇāt teyvat tēvaki pulampiya pulampal</l>
<l>kolli kāvalaṉ mālaṭi muṭimēṟ kōla māṅkula cēkaraṉ coṉṉa</l>
<l>nalli caittamiḻ mālaival lārkaḷ  naṇṇu vārollai nāraṇa ṉulakē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master the good musical Tamil garland—</l>
<l rend="indent">by Kulacēkaraṉ, the guardian of Kolli, whose crown of the head is embellished by Māl’s feet,</l>
<l rend="indent">who uttered the lament cried out by</l>
<l rend="indent">the divine Devakī, who did not see the deeds of limitless maya of</l>
<l rend="indent">[her] Son, who came [to her] thus,</l>
<l rend="indent">having dispatched to heaven the chief of the great, rich city</l>
<l>—shall rapidly reach Nārayaṇa’s world itself.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
